## 2026-03-27 - ColorPicker alpha numeric input doesn't validate range
- Added local editing state (`alphaInput` + `alphaEditing` ref) to decouple the alpha text input from the `alpha` state during typing. The input now accepts any text while focused and only commits/clamps on blur or Enter. Out-of-range values (e.g. "999") are visibly corrected to "100%" at commit time, eliminating the confusing mid-type mismatch. Arrow keys still nudge by 1% and onFocus selects all for easy replacement.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/ColorPicker.tsx` ~L201 (state), ~L228 (prop sync), ~L237 (emit sync), ~L481 (input element)
